-- Bordier Private Bank Client Assets Climb 5%, l’Agefi Reports
-- B y   G i l e s   B r o o m
-- 2012-01-11T10:28:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-11/bordier-private-bank-client-assets-climb-5-l-agefi-reports.html
Bordier & Cie. increased assets
under management by 5 percent to 9.8 billion Swiss francs ($10.3
billion) last year, l’Agefi reported, citing an interview with
Gregoire Bordier, a managing partner at the firm.  The Geneva-based bank aims to increase client assets at its
Singapore office to 1 billion francs from 400 million francs,
the Swiss newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Giles Broom in Geneva at   gbroom@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Frank Connelly at   fconnelly@bloomberg.net  